The central aim of the book is to investigate how Argentine cinema negotiates the argentinidad of Jewish Argentines, thereby adding to the mosaic that is the imagined community of Argentina. To this end, key films by both Jewish and non-Jewish directors are scrutinized, shedding light on three main areas: the masculinity of the Jewish gaucho, the effects of the 1994 AMIA bombing and family relations, including fatherhood and the intermarriage between Jews and Gentiles. Organized around these topics, the book comprises four chapters and with the exception of the first, which is a historical exposition of Jewish presence in Argentina and Argentine film, all subsequent ones take a theme-centered approach. Mirna Vohnsen is a faculty member in Spanish and Latin American Studies at Maynooth University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJews in motion pictures. 0aMotion pictureszArgentinaxHistoryy21st century. 4aFilm & Theatre. 4aHispanic Studies. 4aJewish Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  aArgentine cinema.  aJewishness.  aJews.  afilms.  aidentity issues.  anational identity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311143102440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781787446038?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781787446038423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781787446038/original  a978-3-11-143102-4  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles